N:paperbanana
D:[paperbanana] Route academic-figure work into the lightest workable PaperBanana mode instead of jumping straight to a full multi-agent generation run. Use when the user needs publication-quality methodology diagrams, statistical plots, figure evaluation, polishing an existing figure, batch/sweep generation, or a full-paper figure package from text or PDF.
G:paperbanana academic-figures diagram-generation statistical-plots multi-agent vlm-as-judge mcp cli publication python plan-then-refine

U[8]:
  Capture one intake packet: artifact class, source, provider keys, and quality need before choosing a mode
  Render data-driven charts with plot or plot-batch first because they need only a VLM key, no image-gen
  Generate a single diagram with generate before reaching for batch, sweep, or orchestrate
  Fix an existing figure with polish or evaluate before paying for a full regeneration
  Treat optimize, auto, iterations, and num-candidates as cost dials raised only on evidence
  Pick the cheapest provider that meets quality since the pipeline is provider-agnostic
  Use venue style packs neurips icml acl ieee instead of hand-tuning aesthetics per run
  Route out to matplotlib, TikZ, a vector editor, or a designer when generative figures are the wrong tool

S[7]{n,action,details}:
  1,Intake,capture artifact class source provider-keys budget and quality need before choosing a mode
  2,Install,bash scripts/install.sh --profile plot|diagram|pdf|studio|mcp|all then set one provider key
  3,Understand pipeline,phase0 optimize then phase1 retriever planner stylist then phase2 visualizer critic loop
  4,Run lightest mode,bash scripts/run.sh plot for data or generate for one diagram add optimize or auto only on evidence
  5,Fix before regenerate,use evaluate to judge or polish to guided-edit an existing figure not a fresh run
  6,Scale,use batch plot-batch sweep or orchestrate only when many figures or a whole paper is the real problem
  7,Expose to agents,bash scripts/run-mcp.sh or the Claude Code skills when agent or IDE access beats a bespoke script

R[8]:
  The smallest workable mode beats a full generation run most of the time
  Statistical plots are the cheapest artifact because they never touch an image-gen provider
  Plan-then-refine keeps the cheap text stage separate from the expensive render stage
  A Critic loop plus VLM-as-Judge evaluation gates quality before claiming publication readiness
  Retrieval-augmented planning uses concrete reference examples instead of a blank prompt
  Venue style packs make aesthetics reproducible rather than hand-tuned per figure
  Cost dials optimize auto iterations candidates should be raised only when a plain run underdelivers
  Generative figures are the wrong tool for exact vector art, trivial charts, or brand-locked design

E[6]{type,command}:
  Plot,bash scripts/run.sh plot --data results.csv --intent "Bar chart of accuracy across benchmarks"
  Diagram,bash scripts/run.sh generate --input method.txt --caption "Overview of our framework"
  Refine,bash scripts/run.sh generate --input method.txt --caption "Overview" --optimize --auto
  Evaluate,bash scripts/run.sh evaluate --generated out.png --reference human.png --context method.txt --caption "Overview"
  Polish,bash scripts/run.sh polish --input figure.png --venue icml --iterations 2
  MCP,bash scripts/run-mcp.sh
